#  System Monitor API with FastAPI, Redis, and Docker

## Overview

System Monitor API is a FastAPI-based backend service for collecting basic Linux system metrics, such as disk usage, CPU usage, memory usage, and system uptime.

The project uses Docker and Docker Compose to provide a consistent development and deployment environment. Redis is integrated for visit counting, caching the latest disk metrics, and keeping a short history of disk usage changes.

This project has also been deployed on AWS, where it was tested successfully in a cloud-based environment.


## Features

- Get CPU usage metrics
- Get memory usage information
- Get disk usage information
- Filter disk results by minimum usage percentage
- Return top N disk partitions by usage
- Get system uptime
- Store the latest disk metrics in Redis
- Keep disk metric history in Redis
- Count health check visits
- Provide structured JSON responses
- Log request method, path, status code, and processing time


## Tech Stack

- Python 3.12
- FastAPI
- Uvicorn
- Redis
- Docker
- Docker Compose
- Pytest
- Flake8
- GitHub Actions


